texts.orig: As the 2013 incentive gate target was not met, no STI is payable to KMP for the financial year.
texts.text: As the 2013 incentive gate target was not met, no STI is payable to KMP for the financial year.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: The Board reviewed the Group's STI arrangements during the year and determined to wind up the existing Plan.
texts.text: The Board reviewed the Group's STI arrangements during the year and determined to wind up the existing Plan.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: The following table sets out how the Group's STI arrangements operated during the 2013 financial year.
texts.text: The following table sets out how the Group's STI arrangements operated during the 2013 financial year.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Annual bonus payments for senior executives with an emphasis on the achievement of annual financial  performance	criteria	for	the	Group	as	well	as	specific	strategic	and	operational	criteria.	For	key	senior	executives	 other than the CEO, the bonus criteria were set by the P&CC. Bonus criteria for the CEO were set by the Board.
texts.text: Annual bonus payments for senior executives with an emphasis on the achievement of annual financial  performance	criteria	for	the	Group	as	well	as	specific	strategic	and	operational	criteria.	For	key	senior	executives	 other than the CEO, the bonus criteria were set by the P&CC. Bonus criteria for the CEO were set by the Board.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: For the 2013 financial year, an incentive gate applied which required a threshold level of financial performance  to be achieved before any bonuses became payable. The incentive gate was set at the achievement of the  Group's budgeted EBIT. This was not achieved in 2013 so no STI was paid.
texts.text: For the 2013 financial year, an incentive gate applied which required a threshold level of financial performance  to be achieved before any bonuses became payable. The incentive gate was set at the achievement of the  Group's budgeted EBIT. This was not achieved in 2013 so no STI was paid.

What were the performance  measures and why were  they chosen?
Three components applied in respect of FY13. LEVEL  Corporate Level (50%) Business Unit Level (25%) Strategic Level (25%)

Three components applied in respect of FY13. LEVEL  COMPONENT  Corporate Level (50%) drives corporate financial results (EBIT) and encourages  senior	management	to	work	together	for	the	overall	 benefit of the Group Business Unit Level (25%) drives business unit financial and other operational metrics  to encourage team behaviour (e.g. EBIT, cost reductions,  audience,	market	position	and	revenue) Strategic Level (25%) indicators of future Group, business unit and personal  success (delivery against milestones and personal  development) to drive the delivery of the Corporate strategy.

What could executives earn  under the STi?

PERFORMANCE LEVEL 'on-target'	performance	-	e.g.	for	EBIT	the	'on- target' performance is typically achievement of  budget or prior year 'maximum'	performance	-	requires	stretching	 performance targets to be met.

Each senior executive had a target opportunity depending on the accountabilities of the role and impact on  Company or business unit performance. There are two levels of performance:  PERFORMANCE LEVEL OPPORTUNITY 'on-target'	performance	-	e.g.	for	EBIT	the	'on- target' performance is typically achievement of  budget or prior year CEO	-	75%	of	fixed	remuneration Other	executive	KMP	-	45%	of	fixed	remuneration 'maximum'	performance	-	requires	stretching	 performance targets to be met.
